Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.72,0:38:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The totality, the complete allincclusive\Nallness
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.48,0:38:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,which is no thing. No thing. It is\Nnothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.07,0:38:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not void. It's all\Nall right.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.40,0:38:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, the Buddha didn't speak of God\Nbecause everybody has belief systems
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.48,0:38:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,about God. and your belief system will\Ncreate what you believe God to be and
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.16,0:38:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be pursuing a projection of your\Nown imagination and and ignorance. So
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.68,0:38:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the Buddha didn't speak of God. He said\Njust forget about that. Find the source
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.32,0:38:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of your own consciousness. That is the\NBuddha nature. Well, unfortunately
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.72,0:39:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,called it the Buddha nature. Uh-uh.\NThat was a mistake too. So you call it
