Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.28,0:42:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,of your even existence much less where\Nthere's no way to return. I realized let
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.56,0:42:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,go of that love. So I it took enormous\Nenor enormous energy, enormous power,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.80,0:42:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,all the power I could summon\Nuh to reinforce that thought and come
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.64,0:42:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,back out of the infinite space of the\Nvoid. But that time it was a conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.24,0:42:56.56,Default,,0,0,0,,experience.\NA less sophisticated or less lucky
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.56,0:43:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,person would be convinced that that is\Nthe ultimate reality and let go of the
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.72,0:43:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,last thought\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.31,0:43:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,become as nothingness\Nwhich is a paradox in itself because
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.92,0:43:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,there's nothing that can become\Nnothingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.59,0:43:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But that experience of nothingness could\Nprobably you could probably hang out
