Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.40,1:07:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't there isn't sufficient meat to\Nthe bones. So some teachings to me are
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.88,1:07:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,just too too much bones.\NUm so anyway you want to calibrate the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.16,1:07:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,level of the teacher or the writing of\Nthe book the the mantra whatever way
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.79,1:07:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you're following\Nthe the direct path the direct path
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.35,1:07:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is through consciousness itself.\NThere is a teacher I hold in high esteem
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.72,1:07:57.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in Korea. If you ask her what school do\Nyou represent? She says none.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.76,1:08:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well right that that sounded good. I\Nsaid, "So what do you do?" She said, "We
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.68,1:08:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,just meditate." Wow, that was great. All\Nright. So her ways then is to discover
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.20,1:08:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth through consciousness itself,\Nwhich is what I wrote about in eye of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.11,1:08:15.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the eye or else I wrote it in I I forget\Nwhich. But
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.35,1:08:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,when you sit down to meditate, you\Nnotice that the mind is constantly
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.71,1:08:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,racing and running around and um a lot\Nof teachings try to teach you how to
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.88,1:08:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,control it. You can't control it. You\Ndon't have any control over the mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.44,1:08:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind uh exists of its own nature and\Nit just runs about and does its own
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.00,1:08:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,thing just like the body does. There's\Nno point to try to control it.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.83,1:08:45.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What you do is you you observe what is\Nwhat is it that's witnessing and aware
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.52,1:08:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,of the thoughts. The first thing to do\Nis realize I'm not the body. The next
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.52,1:08:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,thing is to realize I am not the\Nthoughts.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.64,1:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You know you're not the thoughts. And\Nyou know you're not the mind because if
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.15,1:09:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you told the mind stop thinking if you\Nwere the mind it would stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:01.75,1:09:06.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Try telling your mind stop thinking.\NCouldn't care less what you said. Goes
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.79,1:09:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,right on thinking.\NNow if you were the mind it would just
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.23,1:09:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,obey you and you would say and it would\Nstop thinking. The fact that it doesn't
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.60,1:09:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,stop thinking is because you you are not\Nthe mind. You the mind belongs to the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.35,1:09:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,world like the body does.\NUh you can tell the body go without
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.31,1:09:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,oxygen but it won't last long.\NThe body is a manifestation of the world
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.67,1:09:39.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and so is the mind and its content is\Nprogrammed by society
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.27,1:09:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh you don't have any control over\Nthat either.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.75,1:09:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a substrate. What is it that\Ngot programmed there? So the innate
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.44,1:09:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,nature of the mind is the hardware. The\Nthoughts are the software. What happens
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.96,1:10:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is the innocent mind comes in\Nconsciousness with no content.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:00.48,1:10:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it has proclivities which are\Nkarmic proclivities but no specific
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.92,1:10:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,content. Then society starts to program\Nit and so the software begins to pour
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.60,1:10:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,in. So when you start to meditate what\Nyou're what's happening is sort of that
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.96,1:10:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,your hardware is looking at your\Nsoftware.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.84,1:10:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The innate innocence the\Nthe capacity for awareness without any
Dialogue: 0,1:10:27.92,1:10:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,content is still existent within you.\NThe only reason you realize that the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.52,1:10:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,mind is thinking is because the\Nthinkingness is happening against the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.23,1:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,background of non-thinkingness.\NThe only reason you can hear sound is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.67,1:10:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because sound occurs against the\Nbackground of silence.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.64,1:10:56.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh the u\Nthe generally the paths to God are
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.96,1:11:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,described as through the heart and\Nthrough the mind. We're going to stop in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.80,1:11:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,about two seconds.\NYou can see that they are combined.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.96,1:11:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to love the way of the mind\Nenough to go through the sacrifice
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.84,1:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because once you get on the edge of the\Nknife, you cannot stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.00,1:11:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The other thing about spiritual work\Nthat people don't understand is it's not
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.23,1:11:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,just a sporadic thing you do now and\Nthen. When you decide to go for it,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.08,1:11:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,you're on the edge of the knife and you\Ncannot stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.67,1:11:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.\NYou let go and surrender everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:36.64,1:11:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Every tone as it arises is let go of.\NYou're not going to sit back and enjoy
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.64,1:11:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the melody of the symphony. Because as\Nthe note arises, you've already let it
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.96,1:11:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,go. You see, you would have to hold it\Nto compare it with the other notes in
Dialogue: 0,1:11:52.56,1:11:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,order to get music out of it. You hear\Nthe sound of the music, but you're not
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.88,1:11:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,going to hear the mu. You hear the\Nsound, but you're not going to hear the
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.44,1:12:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,music. You're going to hear the tone.\NCan it be done?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.15,1:12:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I don't know. Yes, it can be done.\NYou see,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:20.48,1:12:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because the real energy behind the love\Nis joy. Yeah, the joy of it isn't just
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.15,1:12:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,the love of God. It's the joy\Nwhich is the love of God. manifests
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.84,1:12:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,within yourself as the joy of spiritual\Nwork. So the real energy that gets you
Dialogue: 0,1:12:39.36,1:12:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,going and keeps you going is the joy of\Nspiritual work itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.64,1:12:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Each instant is the source of its own\Njoy. So you have no need for anything
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.28,1:12:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,out in the world. You see joy arises\Nfrom the awareness of the divinity of
Dialogue: 0,1:12:58.23,1:13:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your existence in this moment.\NTherefore, as you walk the edge of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.44,1:13:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,knife, you're outside of time.\NTime is irrelevant. When you're on a
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.48,1:13:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,tight rope,\Ntime, space, all the stuff that the mind
Dialogue: 0,1:13:13.44,1:13:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,usually plays with is no longer\Nrelevant. You're just fixed. Like
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.19,1:13:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the other analogy I use for it is like\Nthe prow of a ship. See, the prow of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:24.23,1:13:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,ship is consistent. No matter what the\Nwave, no matter how high the wave, no
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.84,1:13:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,matter what the wind.\NSo your it's called one-pointedness of
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.12,1:13:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,mind. So that onepointedness of mind is\Na fixity of intention.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.44,1:13:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It gets its energy from the surrender\Nthe devotion to the joy of the presence
Dialogue: 0,1:13:44.15,1:13:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,of God which you intuit it but which\Ndoes not become a stunning awareness
Dialogue: 0,1:13:50.08,1:13:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,until the mind disappears.\NIn theta, the background being that
